$group
    {
        id "FSA-CR 2.8A"
        check_description "Components shall provide the capability to generate audit records relevant to
            +b security for the following categories: access control, request errors, control
            +b system events, backup and restore event, configuration changes, and audit log
            +b events."
        requirement_id "IEC 62443-4-2: CR 2.8(a)-(f)"
        title "Auditable Events - Categories"
        description "This requirement mandates the capability of a component to generate audit
            +b records for events that are significant to the security of the system. It
            +b outlines the categories of events that must be auditable to ensure the
            +b integrity, confidentiality, and availability of the industrial system."
        [ key_aspects
            {
                aspect "Event Categories"
                details "The requirement specifies categories of events that should be auditable,
                    +b including but not limited to: user access, use of privileges, system
                    +b configuration changes, and security function anomalies."
            {
                aspect "Audit Record Generation"
                details "Components must be able to generate audit records automatically for these
                    +b categories of events. The system should ensure that these records are
                    +b comprehensive and include necessary details such as time of occurrence, type of
                    +b event, and the identity of users or systems involved."
            {
                aspect "Security Significance"
                details "The events chosen for auditing should be significant to the security of the
                    +b system, helping to detect unauthorized activities or anomalies that could
                    +b jeopardize system integrity or data confidentiality."
        [ related_standards
            {
                standard "ISO/IEC 27002:2013"
                reference "Section 12.4 - Logging and Monitoring"
                details "This section emphasizes the importance of logging and monitoring information
                    +b systems to detect and respond to security incidents. It provides guidelines on
                    +b logging policies, log management, and the protection of log information."
            {
                standard "NIST SP 800-53 Rev 5"
                reference "AU-2 - Auditable Events"
                details "This control focuses on the identification of events that require auditing and
                    +b the development of audit record generation capabilities. It aligns closely with
                    +b IEC 62443-4-2 CR 2.8 in terms of establishing categories of auditable events."
            {
                standard "ISO/IEC 15408-2:2008"
                reference "Security Functional Requirements - FAU_GEN.1"
                details "The Common Criteria standard specifies functional requirements for audit data
                    +b generation, which includes the ability to generate audit records for
                    +b security-relevant events. It provides a framework similar to the auditing
                    +b requirements in IEC 62443-4-2."
    {
        id "FSA-CR 2.8B"
        check_description "Individual audit records shall include timestamp, source (originating device,
            +b software process or human user account), category, type, event ID, and event
            +b result."
        requirement_id "IEC 62443-4-2: CR 2.8(a)-(f)"
        title "Auditable Events - Data Fields"
        description "This requirement specifies the need to ensure that sufficient data fields are
            +b included in the logs of auditable events to support the analysis of security
            +b incidents. It emphasizes capturing relevant information to facilitate audit and
            +b incident investigation processes."
        { key_aspects
            [ data_fields
                "Timestamp of the event"
                "Source and destination IP address"
                "User identity associated with the event"
                "Type of event and event outcome"
                "Affected system components"
                "Additional context or metadata relevant to the event"
            purpose "To enable comprehensive auditing and forensic analysis in the event of a
