                    +b selection of key data fields and their role in security event analysis."
            { "NERC CIP-007-6"
                section "R4"
                description "Addresses security event monitoring and logging, highlighting the necessity to
                    +b log specific data elements to support security assessments."
            { "PCI DSS"
                section "10"
                description "Stipulates the implementation of logging mechanisms to track and monitor all
                    +b access to network resources and cardholder data, specifying essential data
                    +b fields to be captured."
    {
        id "FSA-CR 2.9A"
        check_description "Components shall provide the capability to allocate audit record storage
            +b capacity according to commonly recognized recommendations for log management."
        requirement_id "IEC 62443-4-2: CR 2.9(a)"
        title "Audit Storage Capacity - Allocation"
        description "This requirement focuses on ensuring that sufficient storage capacity is
            +b allocated for audit records. The aim is to maintain a reliable trail of audit
            +b data that can be used for subsequent analysis and forensic investigation.
            +b Proper allocation helps in ensuring that audit data is not lost due to
            +b insufficient storage capacity."
        { key_aspects
            storage_capacity_planning "Organizations must plan and allocate adequate storage capacity based on the
                +b expected volume of audit records. This involves estimating the volume of audit
                +b data generated over time and ensuring that storage solutions can accommodate
                +b this data."
            scalability "The storage system should be scalable to accommodate increasing volumes of
                +b audit data as the system grows or as audit requirements evolve."
            retention_policies "Define and implement retention policies for audit data to manage storage
                +b capacity efficiently. This includes determining how long audit records need to
                +b be stored and ensuring that obsolete data is archived or deleted according to
                +b policy."
            "real-time monitoring" "Implement real-time monitoring to ensure that storage capacity is not exceeded
                +b and that audit data is recorded without interruption."
            "data integrity" "Ensure the integrity of audit records by implementing measures that prevent
                +b unauthorized changes to stored audit data."
        { related_standards
            { "ISO/IEC 27001"
                clause_12.4.1 "Logging and monitoring, which requires the implementation of logs to record
                    +b user activities, exceptions, and information security events, relevant to audit
                    +b storage considerations."
            { "NIST SP 800-53"
                AU-4 "Audit Storage Capacity, which emphasizes the need for organizations to allocate
                    +b sufficient audit record storage capacity and establish a process for managing
                    +b and modifying the capacity as needed."
            { "CIS Controls"
                "Control 6" "Maintenance, Monitoring, and Analysis of Audit Logs, which includes
                    +b recommendations for ensuring sufficient storage capacity for audit logs."
    {
        id "FSA-CR 2.9B"
