        requirement_id "IEC 62443-4-2: CR 2.9 RE(1)"
        title "Warn When Audit Record Storage Capacity Threshold Reached"
        description "This requirement mandates that a system should be capable of issuing warnings
            +b when the storage capacity for audit records approaches a certain predefined
            +b threshold. This ensures that appropriate actions can be taken to prevent loss
            +b of audit data, which is critical for maintaining the security and integrity of
            +b the system."
        [ key_aspects
            {
                aspect "Audit Record Management"
                details "The system should have a mechanism to monitor the storage capacity dedicated to
                    +b audit logs and generate warnings as it approaches the set threshold."
            {
                aspect "Threshold Configuration"
                details "Administrators should be able to configure the threshold level at which
                    +b warnings are triggered, allowing them to tailor the system's response to their
                    +b specific needs."
            {
                aspect "Notification Mechanism"
                details "The system must support a reliable notification mechanism to alert relevant
                    +b personnel when the threshold is reached. This could include email alerts,
                    +b dashboard notifications, or integration with centralized monitoring systems."
            {
                aspect "Preventive Measures"
                details "By warning administrators before audit record storage is exhausted, the system
                    +b allows for preventive measures such as increasing storage capacity, archiving
                    +b old logs, or adjusting logging levels."
        [ related_standards
            {
                standard "ISO/IEC 27001:2013"
                reference "A.12.4 Logging and Monitoring"
                description "This control emphasizes the importance of event logging and monitoring, which
                    +b aligns with the need to manage and maintain sufficient audit record storage to
                    +b ensure continued logging activities."
            {
                standard "NIST SP 800-92"
                reference "Guide to Computer Security Log Management"
                description "Provides guidance on the establishment of log management infrastructures,
